John stopped breathing as we were about to be discharged, we were all packed to go and the were running one last test so we could go home and John stopped breathing, after that episode he was sent immediately to the NICU. Walking into the NICU for the first time was terrifying and overwhelming. 10 months later the NICU was not a strange scary place. My son served a mission for the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints and finally came home on Friday. He left when his little brother was 2 weeks old and met his little sister for the first time on Friday. John has not left his side and is happy to have two personal jungle gyms at his disposal. June is loving all the snuggles. We even let him change his first diaper on Saturday, lucky guy. I wanted to document this moment but also be present and not have the stress of trying to capture it for my son.  He wanted it video tapped and I wanted everyone to focus on him and be in the moment. I was grateful to be able to find someone to help capture this moment for my son and our family who couldn’t be there. Here are a few stills I was sent from some of the video taken. #homecoming #missionaryhomecoming #family

Today would have been June’s 1st birthday. She was born at 26 weeks weighing 1 pound 11 ounces with Trisomy 21 (which is Down Syndrome), a complete AVSD (instead of having four chambers in your heart she had one). After 130 days in the NICU and two surgeries, June was sent home with oxygen levels around 70-80% because of her heart condidtion that was the best she could maintain. After 6 months of trying to get her big enough she had her open heart surgery at 6 months old on St Patricks day. Due dates are important to mothers of premature babies becuase sometime milestones and development might be delayed due to how early they are born. June’s adjusted age is 1 today, even though she is actually 15.5 months old. She was born 3.5 months early, we never even made it to the third trimester. Today she has surpassed everyone expectations, she is crawling, pulling up on furniture, trying to cruise around, clapping, saying dada, loves to babble and talk, smile at everyone she sees, she loves i hugs, kisses and snuggles with everyone she meets. I am honored to be her mom. Thank you Ranjani owner of Grace Photography PDX for capturign these precious moments for us.  @gracephotographypdx #preemie #micropreemie #avsd #downsyndrome #barbie #mattel #inclusion @barbie @mattel
